## Development Workflows

[CUSTOMIZE: Add your team's workflows]

### TDD Loop (Test-Driven Development)

```bash
# 1. Write failing test
[create_test_file]
[test_command]  # Should fail

# 2. Implement feature
[edit_source_file]

# 3. Run test again
[test_command]  # Should pass

# 4. Refactor if needed

# 5. Run full suite
[test_all_command]
```

### Feature Addition Workflow

```bash
# 1. Create feature branch
git checkout -b feature/my-feature

# 2. [Add your implementation steps]
# Example: Add route, create handler, write tests

# 3. Write tests
[create_test_file]

# 4. Run tests
[test_command]

# 5. Format code
[format_command]

# 6. Commit
git commit -m "feat: add my feature"
```

### Bug Fix Workflow

```bash
# 1. Reproduce bug with test
[create_failing_test]

# 2. Fix bug
[edit_source]

# 3. Verify fix
[test_command]

# 4. Run full suite (check for regressions)
[test_all_command]

# 5. Commit
git commit -m "fix: resolve issue with X"
```

